    • hermTranspose

      public CTensor hermTranspose​(int... axes)
      Computes the conjugate transpose of this tensor. That is, interchanges the axes of this tensor so that it matches the specified axes permutation and takes the complex conjugate of the elements of these axes. Same as H(int[]).
      Specified by:
      hermTranspose in interface ComplexTensorExclusiveMixin<CTensor>
      Parameters:
      axes - Permutation of tensor axis. If the tensor has rank N, then this must be an array of length N which is a permutation of {0, 1, 2, ..., N-1}.
      Returns:
      The conjugate transpose of this tensor with its axes permuted by the axes array.
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - If axes is not a permutation of {1, 2, 3, ... N-1}.
